                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Probability and Statistics Individual (5 problems) "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                329,
                127,
                702,
                175
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. A submarine is lost in some ocean. There are two (and only two) possible regions: A and B. Experts estimate the probability of being lost in A is 70%. On the other hand, for each search, the probability of finding this submarine is 40% if it is lost in A. This number is 80% for region B. Now we have independently searched region A 4 times and region B once, but still have not found the submarine yet. Now based on these informations, which region we should search next? And why? "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                177,
                890,
                281
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2. A teacher and 12 students sit around a circle. In the beginning the teach holds a gift, he will randomly pass it to the left person or right person next to him, so as the other students each time. (For the gift, It is like a random walk between these people) The rule is that the gift will be eventually given to some student (not teacher) if he/she "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                282,
                889,
                369
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is the last student who ever touches the gift. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                321,
                369,
                712,
                386
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Which student(s) have the highest probability to get this gift (i.e., win) ? "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                390,
                781,
                407
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 3. In a party, "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "people attend, each of them brings "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "gifts. When they leave, each of them randomly picks "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "gifts. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the total number of gifts which are taken back by their owners. Let’s fix "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", please find the limiting distribution of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "when "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N \\to \\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                411,
                889,
                479
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 4. Suppose that a random vector "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "{ \\bf x } = ( x _ { 1 } , . . . , x _ { n } ) ^ { \\prime } \\in R ^ { n } ( n \\geq 2 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is distributed as a multivariate normal distribution "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N ( \\mathbf { 0 } , { \\boldsymbol { \\Sigma } } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with the following joint probability density function "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                483,
                889,
                533
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "f (\\mathbf {x}) = \\frac {1}{(2 \\pi) ^ {\\frac {n}{2}} d e t (\\boldsymbol {\\Sigma}) ^ {\\frac {1}{2}}} \\exp \\left\\{- \\frac {1}{2} \\mathbf {x} ^ {\\prime} \\boldsymbol {\\Sigma} ^ {- 1} \\mathbf {x} \\right\\}, \\mathbf {x} \\in R ^ {n},",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/1b43e2445916f81f8e656230f145f73d52326847644d4abeb85c4827b18a46d0.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                297,
                533,
                732,
                571
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Sigma"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is an "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n \\times n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "positive definite matrix. Let the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( i , j )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "element of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Omega = \\Sigma ^ { - 1 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\omega _ { i j }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( 1 \\leq i , j \\leq n )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". For "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1 \\leq i \\neq j \\leq n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", show that if "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\omega _ { i j } = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", then "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x _ { j }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are conditionally independent when the other elements of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { x }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are given. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                574,
                889,
                626
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5. Letx, y be two independent random vectors in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "R ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "( "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n \\geq 3"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "). Assume that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "P ( \\mathbf { y } = \\mathbf { 0 } ) = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { x }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "has a standard multivariate normal distribution, i.e., "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { x } \\sim N ( 0 , I _ { n } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". (a) For any nonzero constant vector "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { a } \\in R ^ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "satisfying "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "| | \\mathbf { a } | | = ( \\mathbf { a } ^ { \\prime } \\mathbf { a } ) ^ { 1 / 2 } = 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", prove that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                629,
                889,
                686
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sqrt {n - 1} \\frac {\\mathbf {a} ^ {\\prime} \\mathbf {x}}{\\sqrt {| | \\mathbf {x} | | ^ {2} - (\\mathbf {a} ^ {\\prime} \\mathbf {x}) ^ {2}}} \\sim t _ {n - 1},",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/d99927cd7d9fd2d32a62ad97f4cbb6fdf032c59a7a9ecf59eb656b3b97fad4eb.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                378,
                690,
                653,
                728
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "here "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "t _ { n - 1 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "stands for a "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "t"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "distribution with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n - 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "degrees of freedom. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                732,
                721,
                749
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(b) The sample correlation coefficient between "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { x } = ( x _ { 1 } , . . . , x _ { n } ) ^ { \\prime }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { y } = ( y _ { 1 } , . . . , y _ { n } ) ^ { \\prime }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is defined as "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                752,
                889,
                784
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "r = \\frac {\\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} (x _ {i} - \\bar {x}) (y _ {i} - \\bar {y})}{\\sqrt {\\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} (x _ {i} - \\bar {x}) ^ {2}} \\sqrt {\\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} (y _ {i} - \\bar {y}) ^ {2}}}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/25da65a321da66a38048afd340a52d34c7455b51669de4ede93db3a6873d027a.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                351,
                783,
                680,
                822
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\textstyle { \\bar { x } } = \\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ { n } x _ { i } / n , { \\bar { y } } = \\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ { n } y _ { i } / n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Show that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sqrt { n - 2 } \\frac { r } { \\sqrt { 1 - r ^ { 2 } } } \\sim t _ { n - 2 }"
                    }
                ]
            },
